        "subtype": "bot_message",
        "text": "*[Bug 17702] Assignment to data.frame column (`$&lt;-` or `[[&lt;-`) should convert POSIXlt to POSIXct*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=17702>\n\nHeather Turner (<mailto:ht@heatherturner.net|ht@heatherturner.net>) changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                 CC|                            |ht@heatherturner.net\n\n--- Comment #2 from Heather Turner (<mailto:ht@heatherturner.net|ht@heatherturner.net>) ---\nFor total consistency, I think `$&lt;-.data.frame` would need to use\n`as.data.frame(x)` to convert back to a data frame rather than reapplying x's\nclass to the intermediate list object.\n\nHowever, you're right that this would be a major shift in behaviour. One\nparticular case that would be affected is matrices\/arrays. Currently a matrix\nis converted to separate columns by `data.frame`\/`as.data.frame` but added as a\nsingle column by `$&lt;-`\/`[[&lt;-`:\n\n```\ndf &lt;- data.frame(arr1 = matrix(1:10, 5, 2))\ndf$arr2 &lt;- matrix(1:10, 5, 2)\nlapply(df, class)\n#&gt; $arr1.1\n#&gt; [1] \"integer\"\n#&gt; \n#&gt; $arr1.2\n#&gt; [1] \"integer\"\n#&gt; \n#&gt; $arr2\n#&gt; [1] \"matrix\" \"array\"\n```\n\nThis is well documented in `?data.frame` and I think there's a lot of code that\nrelies on this behaviour in the wild. So I think Approach 1 is probably out.\n\nI'm not sure about special-casing POSIXlt to coerce to POSIXct in `$&lt;-`\/`[[&lt;-`.\nAt the moment `$&lt;-`\/`[[&lt;-` don't do any coercion when replacing a whole column.\nIn some ways it would be better if `data.frame`\/`as.data.frame` did not coerce\nPOSIXlt in the first place, then users would be encouraged to explictly convert\nto POSIXct as required, leading to more understandable code. Such a change\nwould  also have broad impact though and is not a decision we could take\nlightly.",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1781104704.663369",
        "bot_id": "B06769YJX9Q",
        "app_id": "A024R9PQM",
        "blocks": [
            {
                "type": "rich_text",
                "block_id": "T=k",
                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "[Bug 17702] Assignment to data.frame column (",
                                "style": {
                                    "bold": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "$<-",
                                "style": {
                                    "bold": true,
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " or ",
                                "style": {
                                    "bold": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "[[<-",
                                "style": {
                                    "bold": true,
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") should convert POSIXlt to POSIXct",
                                "style": {
                                    "bold": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=17702"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nHeather Turner ("
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "mailto:ht@heatherturner.net",
                                "text": "ht@heatherturner.net"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") changed:\n\n           What    |Removed                     |Added\n----------------------------------------------------------------------------\n                 CC|                            |ht@heatherturner.net\n\n--- Comment #2 from Heather Turner ("
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "mailto:ht@heatherturner.net",
                                "text": "ht@heatherturner.net"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") ---\nFor total consistency, I think "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "$<-.data.frame",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " would need to use\n"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "as.data.frame(x)",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " to convert back to a data frame rather than reapplying x's\nclass to the intermediate list object.\n\nHowever, you're right that this would be a major shift in behaviour. One\nparticular case that would be affected is matrices\/arrays. Currently a matrix\nis converted to separate columns by "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "data.frame",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\/"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "as.data.frame",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " but added as a\nsingle column by "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "$<-",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\/"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "[[<-",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ":\n\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "df <- data.frame(arr1 = matrix(1:10, 5, 2))\ndf$arr2 <- matrix(1:10, 5, 2)\nlapply(df, class)\n#> $arr1.1\n#> [1] \"integer\"\n#> \n#> $arr1.2\n#> [1] \"integer\"\n#> \n#> $arr2\n#> [1] \"matrix\" \"array\"\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nThis is well documented in "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "?data.frame",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " and I think there's a lot of code that\nrelies on this behaviour in the wild. So I think Approach 1 is probably out.\n\nI'm not sure about special-casing POSIXlt to coerce to POSIXct in "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "$<-",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\/"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "[[<-",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ".\nAt the moment "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "$<-",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\/"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "[[<-",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " don't do any coercion when replacing a whole column.\nIn some ways it would be better if "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "data.frame",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\/"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "as.data.frame",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " did not coerce\nPOSIXlt in the first place, then users would be encouraged to explictly convert\nto POSIXct as required, leading to more understandable code. Such a change\nwould  also have broad impact though and is not a decision we could take\nlightly."
                            }
                        ]
